  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Setting a good foundation for Organizational Growth and Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ndaroini PLC is a farmer led business whose focus is production and marketing of coffee.The company structure is fairly young with relatively under developed institutional structure ranging from financial management and governance as well as HR services.Therefore majority of the activities planned for this period targets to strengthen the organization structure of Ndaroini PLC by instituting the basic organizational structures. Additionally  a clear strategy will be developed to guide the strategic direction of Ndaroini for the next 3-5 years.Ndaroini is currently engaged in a tri-patriate agreement with Rabo Foundation and Trabocca BV. Trabocca is the offtaker for all of the coffee produced by Ndaroini. Based on this contract  Rabo Foundation has received a working capital loan(USD 250 000) to facilitate the farmers access inputs on credit as well as provide farmers with a coffee picking advance. This is paid with one bullet payment once the coffee payout is received from Ndaroini. As a result of this partnership  RF has engaged Agriterra to provide TA service to build the capacity of Ndaroini to bankability. This will target to enable Ndaroini build its institutional capacity and be able to borrow commercial loans in future.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strategic planAgronomistERP systemInternal control systems</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This plan focuses on fixing the basic institutional gaps at Ndaroini. For this reason  the first will be targeted on strengthening the institutional capacity on Governance  Financial management and production and agronomy to spur the organization towards sustainable increase in yields. This will form a basis to build bankable business in the coming period.</narrative>
  </description>
